# Exxat DS ‚Äî package publish validation (agents + maintainers)

**Applies when:** bumping `@exxatdesignux/ui` or `@exxatdesignux/product-framework` versions, running `pnpm release`, or answering "publish the package".

## One builder app + one generated starter payload

| App | Path | Role |
|-----|------|------|
| **Builder / dogfood** | `apps/web` | What we run at `pnpm dev` (port 4000) ‚Äî **edit shell here** |
| **Generated starter payload** | `packages/ui/template-vite/` | What npm + `exxat-ui init` / `upgrade` copy from ‚Äî **generated, not a second app; do not hand-edit for parity** |

**MUST** run sync after any builder-shell change **before** publish:

```bash
pnpm builder:contract        # proves apps/web is wired to local DS + manifest is complete
pnpm sync-ui-template          # apps/web ‚Üí generated starter payload (apply)
pnpm sync-ui-template:check    # fails if still drifted
```

`pnpm release:gates` runs the builder contract, dogfood build, sync apply + check, and publish smoke automatically ‚Äî agents still run sync explicitly when they edited `apps/web` so the tree is committed before gates.

## External workspace (MUST ‚Äî outside monorepo)

Publish smoke **MUST NOT** scaffold inside `DS_Workspace V2` or OS `/tmp`.

**Default root:**

`/Users/himanshusuthar/Exxat Projects/Design System/123_Testing`

| Subfolder | Contents |
|-----------|----------|
| `tarballs/` | `pnpm pack` output |
| `apps/` | Temp consumer scaffolds |

Override: `EXXAT_PUBLISH_SMOKE_ROOT=/other/path`

## MUST NOT

- **Publish after a version bump only** ‚Äî no `pnpm release` until gates pass.
- **Hand-edit `template-vite/`** for shell parity when the change belongs in `apps/web` ‚Äî it is a generated starter payload; sync instead.
- **Skip sync** because `apps/web` ‚Äúlooks fine‚Äù ‚Äî consumers get the generated starter payload, not dogfood paths.
- **Assume prior `release:gates`** ‚Äî re-run after `apps/web`, `template-vite`, `bin/`, or `package.json` `files` changes.

## MUST (agent order before every publish)

1. **Finish builder work** in `apps/web` (routes, nav, settings shell, sidebar, etc.).
2. **`pnpm builder:contract`** ‚Äî prove `apps/web` consumes local DS (`workspace:*` + Vite source resolver) and the sync manifest is complete.
3. **`pnpm sync-ui-template`** ‚Äî copy shell into the generated starter payload.
4. **`pnpm sync-ui-template:check`** ‚Äî zero drift (or rely on gates step 2‚Äì3).
5. **`pnpm release:gates`** or **`pnpm --filter @exxatdesignux/ui smoke-test:publish`** ‚Äî includes builder build, sync + `123_Testing` consumer sim.
6. **`pnpm release`** (maintainer npm OTP).

**Publish smoke proves:** synced generated starter in tarball ‚Üí temp app in `123_Testing` ‚Üí `exxat-ui upgrade` preserves builder-owned content/data ‚Üí build ‚Üí dev boot.

**Tell consumers:** `upgrade` refreshes predefined Prism / One / Design OS shell and navigation from the generated starter while preserving builder-owned tenant catalog, data modules, mock/API wiring, and custom pages.

## Agent checklist (state in chat)

- [ ] Shell changes landed in **`apps/web`** (not only template-vite)
- [ ] **`pnpm builder:contract`** green
- [ ] Ran **`pnpm sync-ui-template`** (builder ‚Üí generated starter)
- [ ] **`sync-template:check`** green
- [ ] Publish smoke used **`123_Testing`** (log: `external workspace (outside monorepo)`)
- [ ] Tarball has `bin/shell-sync-manifest.mjs`; **`exxat-ui upgrade`** OK; dev boot OK
- [ ] `packages/ui/package.json` version matches `RELEASES.md`

